div.div:
Add review feature to ReportedAttachments
This commit introduces a review feature to the 'ReportedAttachments' model. New fields 'reviewed' and 'reviewed_by' have been added and are reflected in the AttachmentReportLayout. Enhances tracking and management of reports, showing if and by whom an attachment was reviewed.

"Update ReportedAttachments model"
This commit modifies the 'ReportedAttachments' model by changing the 'message' field to 'messages' and setting its cast to 'string'. The field renaming will make it more consistent with the rest of the application and type casting will ensure the data interactions are handled correctly.

Remove unused Model import and variable in AttachmentReportReview
Unused Model, ReportReview, was removed from the AttachmentReportReview.php file. Additionally, an unused variable, 'review', was also removed. These changes improve the cleanliness and efficiency of the code by removing unused declarations. The reference to $this->review attachment_id also updated to $this->case->attachment_id, ensuring that the correct data is being accessed.

Change message field type and rename in migrations and attachment reviews
The migration files have been updated to change the type of the 'message' field from 'string' to 'longText'. Additionally, the field has been renamed to 'messages' in AttachmentReportReview. These changes offer more flexibility for storing longer texts and establish consistency in naming across the application.

Add fillable fields to ReportedAttachments and event to AttachmentReportReview.
Extended the ReportedAttachments model by including more fillable fields. Also, added a new event in AttachmentReportReview to invoke the UpdateAudit on a successful review. The update is designed to essentially aid in keeping track of the review reports.
